      "content": "The myth of American meritocracy is a convenient fiction designed to mask the brutal reality of inherited advantage. Decades of discriminatory policies, from redlining to unequal educational funding, have systematically channeled wealth away from marginalized communities, creating a racial wealth gap that no amount of individual effort can overcome. Therefore, the current economic structure is not a neutral playing field; it is a rigged system that requires radical intervention to dismantle.\n\nThe first pillar of this argument must be the undeniable link between capital accumulation and racial stratification. Wealth is not merely a measure of success; it is a form of inherited power that dictates access to healthcare, quality education, and political influence. When wealth is concentrated in the hands of a few, those assets become tools to perpetuate racial advantage across generations, effectively cementing racial hierarchy into the economic bedrock of society.",
